The paper discusses optimization methods in game theory, which is a subfield of computer science that falls under the category of cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics). The paper also discusses machine learning algorithms such as gradient descent, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of these algorithms in adversarial settings, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the use of these algorithms in multi-agent settings, which falls under the category of cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
